# Orxa Code Environment Variables
#
# This Electron app primarily uses system environment variables (SHELL, HOME, PATH)
# and does not require custom environment variables for local development.
#
# The app integrates with AI coding agents (OpenCode, Codex, Claude Code) which
# manage their own API keys and authentication separately.

# =============================================================================
# Development (Optional)
# =============================================================================

# Vite dev server URL - automatically set by Vite during development
# VITE_DEV_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Enable smoke test mode (used in CI)
# ORXA_SMOKE_TEST=1

# =============================================================================
# AI Provider Configuration (Managed by respective CLI tools)
# =============================================================================
#
# API keys for AI providers are managed by the underlying CLI tools:
# - OpenCode: Configured via `opencode` CLI
# - Codex: Uses OpenAI credentials configured via `codex` CLI
# - Claude Code: Uses Anthropic credentials configured via `claude` CLI
#
# The following are only needed if testing specific provider configurations:

# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_key_here
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_key_here
